title: Drawing, "End Table", ca. 1935
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Stamp in black ink, lower right: DONALD DESKEY/630 FIFTH AVENUE/NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at lower left: ALL ROSEWOOD VENEERED/FINISH ALL AROUND; inscribed in graphite at lower right: SCALE 1"=1'0/8603 [circled and crossed out]/SEE NEW SCALE DRAW; dimensions in graphite
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing for end table against a side chair or sofa. Rectangular, horizontal table in rosewood veneer with three shelves that extend beyond top surface.
